  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SMART coffee project (Sustainable Marketing of Arabica through Technology)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coffee Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In order to achieve this goal, the project will use a two-pronged approach to strengthen the farmer organizations to market higher quality and quantity of coffee, while at the same time supporting smallholder farmers enhance productivity, through increased resilience, credit access, investment, and technology adoption through the use of ICT.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project is that GCCE consistently and increasingly meets buyer quality and quantity demand.  The main objective of the project is that GCCE exports high quality and sufficient quantity of coffee for its members.

This strategic objective will be achieved through the following outcomes, outputs and activities:
 
Outcome 1: Coffee farmers use knowledge and resources to improve the quantity and quality of their production
 Output 1.1: Targeted farmers have access to qualified and effective extension support
 Output 1.2: Targeted farmers have access to inputs 

Output 1.3: Targeted farmers access information and technology to improve value 
addition and reduce post-harvest losses 

Outcome 2: Coffee farmers use financial services (credit, savings, and insurance, payments) to increase their agricultural investments
 Output 2.1: Targeted farmers have improved access to savings, loans and other financial
 services for agricultural investments 
Output 2.2: Targeted farmers and other value chain actors receive timely payments
 
Outcome 3: Coffee farmers receive sustainable and equitable services from GCCE and the PS to which they belong
 Output 3.1: GCCE and member PS have organizational policies, procedures, and 
outreach practices that improve the operations of the organizations 
Output 3.2: GCCE and PS have a credible system for collective procurement of inputs and payment for coffee deliveries</narrative>
  </description>
